overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request with numerous
  issues, including critical security flaws, failing Vercel deploys, and various
  functional bugs. The agent began by identifying all reported issues, including
  a trivially forgeable admin authentication cookie, arbitrary pagination values
  in API routes, memory issues with CSV export, PDF generation errors (NaN
  values, missing minutes, hardcoded user), inert download buttons, and missing
  time validation. The agent systematically addressed each issue, starting with
  lint errors and then moving to security and functional fixes. A crucial
  decision was made to refactor the HMAC-based session management to use the Web
  Crypto API, ensuring compatibility with Vercel's Edge Runtime for middleware
  after a build warning was encountered. This proactive fix prevented potential
  deployment failures. The outcome is a significantly more secure, stable, and
  functional sleep questionnaire application with all identified issues resolved
  and a successful build and deployment path established.
